HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1159
By Martin B
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Huntingdon High
School Fillies girls' basketball team upon winning
the 2026 TSSAA Division I, Class 2A state
championship.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this General Assembly should salute those student athletes
who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as true champions of
whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary group of young ladies is the Fillies girls' basketball
team of Huntingdon High School, whose members have proven themselves to be the fiercest of
competitors and truly worthy of admiration by winning the 2026 TSSAA Division I, Class 2A
state championship; and
WHEREAS, the Fillies roster was not packed with experience when the season began,
as it included six sophomores, four freshmen, and a lone senior; and
WHEREAS, despite their lack of experience, the 2025-2026 Fillies dominated the
opposition, winning a school-record 31 games; after suffering their final loss on December 20,
2025, Huntingdon finished the season with a 21-game winning streak; and
WHEREAS, the Fillies began postseason play by winning the District 12-AA tournament,
trouncing Waverly 78-29 in the semifinals and routing Camden 65-20 in the championship tilt;
and
WHEREAS, at the Region 6-AA tournament, Huntingdon blasted Harpeth 91-26 in the
quarterfinals, demolished Cheatham County 57-22 in the semifinals, and defeated Stewart
County 54-47 in the final to claim the region title and earn a coveted home game in the sectional
round; and
HJR1159
015957
- 1 -

WHEREAS, facing off against Summertown in their sectional contest, Huntingdon
posted a 20-point victory (65-45) to punch their ticket to The Glass House, home of the TSSAA
Class 2A state tournament; and
WHEREAS, as the competition toughened, so did the Fillies; Huntingdon avenged one
of only three losses all year by defeating Smith County 60-57 in the quarterfinals before
vanquishing Gatlinburg-Pittman 65 42 in the semifinal round of the state tourney; and
WHEREAS, matching up against the always-tough York Institute in the title game, the
Fillies slayed the Dragonettes 43-41 and raised the Gold Ball trophy as state champions; and
WHEREAS, the Fillies relied heavily upon the talent, leadership, and determination of
their freshman phenom Wylie Kee throughout the season, and especially in the state
tournament; and
WHEREAS, Wylie Kee averaged 19.4 points and 8.4 rebounds per game for the season,
but truly spread her wings in the state tournament, scoring 54 points and pulling down 39
rebounds; and
WHEREAS, Wylie Kee's roundball prowess is self-evident, but she has also received
numerous honors; she was named Most Valuable Player of the District 12-AA regular season,
District 12-AA tournament, Region 6-AA tournament, and the Class 2A state tournament, and
she was also named a Miss Basketball finalist this season; and
WHEREAS, Huntingdon's superb performance would not have been possible without the
expert guidance of Coach David Wilkins; his assistants, Kelsey Perry and Cliff Kelley; and the
unfailing support of the players' families, their fans, and their community; and
WHEREAS, Coach Wilkins has posted an outstanding overall record of 166-54 with
three state tournament appearances during his seven years as head coach of the Fillies; the
2026 state title is his first, an accomplishment that should relieve some pressure within the
Wilkins family, as his father and two brothers have won five state titles between them; and
- 2 - 015957

WHEREAS, each of the Fillies players contributed significantly to the team's remarkable
winning streak en route to the state title; these outstanding young ladies include the
aforementioned Wylie Kee, All-State Tournament selection Ellie Wilson, the team's second-
leading scorer Knox Bennett, Grier Bartholomew, Krystin Moore, Kaylen Cary, Millie Luther,
Tatum Rich, Emalynn Maness, Ali Harris, and Maria Baretto de Vicente; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Huntingdon girls' basketball team epitomize all that is
good in today's student athletes, as they have achieved a premier level of success in
competition while exhibiting the highest degree of character in all aspects of life; and
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly find it appropriate to acknowledge
and applaud the Huntingdon Fillies for their championship season on the hardwood; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the Huntingdon High School Fillies girls'
basketball team upon winning the 2026 TSSAA Division I, Class 2A state championship and
extend to them our best wishes for every continued success in all their future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
